title: Michelle Steel
added: In 2014, a video showed Steel speaking at a Tea Party event in [[Newport Beach, California|Newport Beach]] about withdrawing her younger daughter from the [[University of California, Santa Cruz]] and sending her to [[Loyola Marymount University|Loyola Marymount]] for a "brainwash" after her daughter voiced support for same-sex marriage and [[Barack Obama]].<ref>{{cite web|date=July 7, 2020|title=Republican congressional candidate bragged about pulling daughter out of university for ‘brainwashing’ after she supported equal marriage|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2020/07/07/michelle-steel-california-orange-county-republican-daughter-university-santa-cruz-equal-marriage/|accessdate=August 21, 2020|website=PinkNews - Gay news, reviews and comment from the world's most read lesbian, gay, bisexual, and trans news service}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bollinger|first1=Alex|date=July 8, 2020|title=Republican candidate brags about pulling her daughter out of college for supporting LGBTQ rights|url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2020/07/republican-candidate-brags-pulling-daughter-college-supporting-lgbtq-rights/|accessdate=August 21, 2020|website=LGBTQ Nation}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=July 8, 2020|title=California GOP congressional candidate claimed she withdrew her daughter from college for supporting gay marriage|url=https://www.metroweekly.com/2020/07/california-gop-congressional-candidate-claimed-she-withdrew-her-daughter-from-college-for-supporting-gay-marriage/|accessdate=August 21, 2020|website=Metro Weekly}}</ref>
